[30;1m517 | [0m[35mthe Python console as a rendered tree.  For single-node search[0m

[30;1m161 | [0m[35m====================[0m
[30;1m162 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35mIn certain scenarios, you may want to stream data to disk, rather than[0m
[30;1m164 | [0m[35mwriting an entire array of data at once.  For example, it may not be[0m
[30;1m165 | [0m[35mpossible to fit the entire array in memory, or you may want to save[0m
[30;1m166 | [0m[35mdata from a device as it comes in to prevent data loss.  The ASDF[0m
[30;1m167 | [0m[35mStandard allows exactly one streaming block per file where the size of[0m

[30;1m75 | [0m[35mclass ArrayNode:[0m
[30;1m76 | [0m[35m    """This class is used to represent unique dummy nodes in the diff tree. In[0m
[30;1m77 | [0m[35m    general these dummy nodes will be list elements that we want to keep track[0m

[30;1m79 | [0m[35m    cleaner."""[0m

[30;1m23 | [0m[35m## Introduction to the Test Suite Structure[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35mThe tests in this suite are contained in the `tests` directory at the root of this repository.[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35mInside that directory is a subdirectory for each released version of the specification.[0m
[30;1m27 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m28 | [0m[35mThe structure and contents of each file in these directories is described below.[0m

[30;1m397 | [0m[35mWhen the module is imported, ``ManifestExtension.from_uri`` asks the `asdf` library to load[0m
[30;1m398 | [0m[35mall available resources so that it can retrieve the manifest content.  But loading the resources[0m

[30;1m282 | [0m[35mOne of the hooks that pyyaml supplies is the ability to overload the method[0m
[30;1m283 | [0m[35m``construct_object``. That's what the class ``yamlutil.AsdfLoader`` does. pyyaml[0m
[30;1m284 | [0m[35mcalls this method at each node in the tree to see if anything special should be[0m
[30;1m285 | [0m[35mdone. One could perform conversion to predefined objects here, but instead it[0m
[30;1m286 | [0m[35mdoes the following: it sees if the node.tag attribute is handled by yaml itself[0m
